obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34628)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34628&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Partnership Act,`
  line 1932.
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[^3***].]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the 1st day of October, 1932, except section 69, which shall come into`
  line `force on the 1st day of October, 1933.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34629)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34629&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) an "act of a firm" means any act or omission by all the partners, or by any partner or agent of`
  line `the firm which gives rise to a right enforceable by or against the firm;`
  line
  line `(b) "business" includes every trade, occupation and profession;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "third party", used in relation to a firm or to a partner therein, means any person who is not a`
  line `partner in the firm; and`
  line
  line `(e) expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of`
  line `1872), shall have the meanings assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34630)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of provisions of Act 9 of 1872.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34630&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The unrepealed provisions of the Indian Contract`
  line `Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), save in so far as they are inconsistent with the express provisions of this Act, shall`
  line `continue to apply to firms.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34631)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Definition of “partnership”, “partner”, “firm” and “firm name”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34631&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `"Partnership" is the relation`
  line `between persons who have agreed to share the profits of a business carried on by all or any of them acting`
  line `for all.`
  line
  line `Persons who have entered into partnership with one another are called individually "partners" and`
  line `collectively "a firm", and the name under which their business is carried on is called the "firm name".`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34632)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Partnership not created by status.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34632&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The relation of partnership arises from contract and not from`
  line status;
  line
  line `and, in particular, the members of a Hindu undivided family carrying on a family business as such, or`
  line `a Burmese Buddhist husband and wife carrying on business as such are not partners in such business.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34633)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Mode of determining existence of partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34633&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `In determining whether a group of persons is or`
  line `is not a firm, or whether a person is or is not a partner in a firm, regard shall be had to the real relation`
  line `between the parties, as shown by all relevant facts taken together.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--The sharing of profits or of gross returns arising from property by persons holding a`
  line `joint or common interest in that property does not of itself make such persons partners.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The receipt by a person of a share of the profits of a business, or of a payment`
  line `contingent upon the earning of profits or varying with the profits earned by a business, does not of itself`
  line `make him a partner with the persons carrying on the business;`
  line
  line `and, in particular, the receipt of such share or payment--`
  line
  line `(a) by a lender of money to persons engaged or about to engage in any business,`
  line
  line `(b) by a servant or agent as remuneration,`
  line
  line `(c) by the widow or child of a deceased partner, as annuity, or`
  line
  line `(d) by a previous owner or part owner of the business, as consideration for the sale of the`
  line `goodwill or share thereof,`
  line
  line `does not of itself make the receiver a partner with the persons carrying on the business.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34634)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Partnership at will.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34634&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where no provision is made by contract between the partners for the`
  line `duration of their partnership or for the determination of their partnership, the partnership is "partnership at`
  line `will".`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34635)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Particular partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34635&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A person may become a partner with another person in particular`
  line `adventures or undertakings.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34636)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `General duties of partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34636&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Partners are bound to carry on the business of the firm to the`
  line `greatest common advantage, to be just and faithful to each other, and to render true accounts and full`
  line `information of all things affecting the firm to any partner or his legal representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34637)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty to indemnify for loss caused by fraud.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34637&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every partner shall indemnify the firm for any`
  line `loss caused to it by his fraud in the conduct of the business of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34638)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Determination of rights and duties of partners by contract between the partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34638&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the mutual rights and duties`
  line `of the partners of a firm may be determined by contract between the partners, and such contract may be`
  line `expressed or may be implied by a course of dealing.`
  line
  line `Such contract may be varied by consent of all the partners, and such consent may be expressed or`
  line `may be implied by a course of dealing.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 27 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872),`
  line `such contracts may provide that a partner shall not carry on any business other than that of the firm while`
  line `he is a partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34639)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `The conduct of the business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34639&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners--`
  line
  line `(a) every partner has a right to take part in the conduct of the business;`
  line
  line `(b) every partner is bound to attend diligently to his duties in the conduct of the business;`
  line
  line `(c) any difference arising as to ordinary matters connected with the business may be decided by a`
  line `majority of the partners, and every partner shall have the right to express his opinion before the matter`
  line `is decided, but no change may be made in the nature of the business without the consent of all the`
  line `partners; and`
  line
  line `(d) every partner has a right to have access to and to inspect and copy any of the books`
  line `of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34640)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Mutual rights and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34640&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners--`
  line
  line `(a) a partner is not entitled to receive remuneration for taking part in the conduct of the business;`
  line
  line `(b) the partners are entitled to share equally in the profits earned, and shall contribute equally to`
  line `the losses sustained by the firm;`
  line
  line `(c) where a partner is entitled to interest on the capital subscribed by him such interest shall be`
  line `payable only out of profits;`
  line
  line `(d) a partner making, for the purposes of the business, any payment or advance beyond the`
  line `amount of capital he has agreed to subscribe, is entitled to interest thereon at the rate of six per cent.`
  line `per annum;`
  line
  line `(e) the firm shall indemnify a partner in respect of payments made and liabilities incurred by`
  line him--
  line
  line `(i) in the ordinary and proper conduct of the business, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in doing such act, in an emergency, for the purpose of protecting the firm from loss, as`
  line `would be done by a person of ordinary prudence, in his own case, under similar circumstances;`
  line and
  line
  line `(f) a partner shall indemnify the firm for any loss caused to it by his wilful neglect in the conduct`
  line `of the business of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34641)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `The property of the firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34641&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners, the property of the firm`
  line `includes all property and rights and interests in property originally brought into the stock of the firm, or`
  line `acquired, by purchase or otherwise, by or for the firm, or for the purposes and in the course of the`
  line `business of the firm, and includes also the goodwill of the business.`
  line
  line `Unless the contrary intention appears, property and rights and interests in property acquired with`
  line `money belonging to the firm are deemed to have been acquired for the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34642)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Application of the property of the firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34642&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners, the property`
  line `of the firm shall be held and used by the partners exclusively for the purposes of the business.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34643)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Personal profits earned by partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34643&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners,--`
  line
  line `(a) if a partner derives any profits for himself from any transaction of the firm, or from the use of`
  line `the property or business connection of the firm or the firm name, he shall account for that profit and`
  line `pay it to the firm;`
  line
  line `(b) if a partner carries on any business of the same nature as and competing with that of the firm,`
  line `he shall account for and pay to the firm all profits made by him in that business.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34701)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Rights and duties of partners— after a change in the firm, after the expiry of the term of the firm, and where additional undertakings are carried out`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34701&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the`
  line partners,--
  line
  line `(a) where a change occurs in the constitution of a firm, the mutual rights and duties of the`
  line `partners in the reconstituted firm remain the same as they were immediately before the change, as far`
  line `as may be;`
  line
  line `(b) where a firm constituted for a fixed term continues to carry on business after the expiry of that`
  line `term, the mutual rights and duties of the partners remain the same as they were before the expiry, so`
  line `far as they may be consistent with the incidents of partnership at will; and`
  line
  line `(c) where a firm constituted to carry out one or more adventures or undertakings carries out other`
  line `adventures or undertakings, the mutual rights and duties of the partners in respect of the other`
  line `adventures or undertakings are the same as those in respect of the original adventures or undertakings.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34645)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Partner to be agent of the firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34645&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a partner is the agent of`
  line `the firm for the purposes of the business of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34646)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Implied authority of partner as agent of the firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34646&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 22,`
  line `the act of a partner which is done to carry on, in the usual way, business of the kind carried on by the`
  line `firm, binds the firm.`
  line
  line `The authority of a partner to bind the firm conferred by this section is called his implied authority--.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of any usage or custom of trade to the contrary, the implied authority of a partner`
  line `does not empower him to--`
  line
  line `(a) submit a dispute relating to the business of the firm to arbitration,`
  line
  line `(b) open a banking account on behalf of the firm in his own name,`
  line
  line `(c) compromise or relinquish any claim or portion of a claim by the firm,`
  line
  line `(d) withdraw a suit or proceeding filed on behalf of the firm,`
  line
  line `(e) admit any liability in a suit or proceeding against the firm,`
  line
  line `(f) acquire immovable property on behalf of the firm,`
  line
  line `(h) transfer immovable property belonging to the firm, or`
  line
  line `(g) enter into partnership on behalf of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34647)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Extension and restriction of partner’s implied authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34647&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The partners in a firm may, by`
  line `contract between the partners, extend or restrict the implied authority of any partner.`
  line
  line `Notwithstanding any such restriction, any act done by a partner on behalf of the firm which falls`
  line `within his implied authority binds the firm, unless the person with whom he is dealing knows of the`
  line `restriction or does not know or believe that partner to be a partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34648)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Partner’s authority in an emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34648&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `A Partner has authority, in an emergency, to do all such`
  line `acts for the purpose of protecting the firm from loss as would be done by a person of ordinary prudence,`
  line `in his own case, acting under similar circumstances, and such acts bind the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34649)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Mode of doing act to bind firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34649&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `In order to bind a firm, an act or instrument done or executed`
  line `by a partner or other person on behalf of the firm shall be done or executed in the firm name, or in any`
  line `other manner expressing or implying an intention to bind the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34702)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Effect of admissions by a partner.,`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34702&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `An admission or representation made by a partner`
  line `concerning the affairs of the firm is evidence against the firm, if it is made in the ordinary course of`
  line business.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34703)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Effect of notice to acting partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34703&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Notice to a partner who habitually acts in the business of the`
  line `firm of any matter relating to the affairs of the firm operates as notice to the firm, except in the case of a`
  line `fraud on the firm committed by or with the consent of that partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34651)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Liability of a partner for acts of the firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34651&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Every partner is liable, jointly with all the other`
  line `partners and also severally, for all acts of the firm done while he is a partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34652)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Liability of the firm for wrongful acts of a partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34652&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where, by the wrongful act or omission`
  line `of a partner acting in the ordinary course of the business of a firm, or with the authority of his partners,`
  line `loss or injury is caused to any third party, or any penalty is incurred, the firm is liable therefor to the same`
  line `extent as the partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34653)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Liability of firm for misapplication by partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34653&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line Where--
  line
  line `(a) a partner acting within his apparent authority receives money or property from a third party`
  line `and misapplies it, or`
  line
  line `(b) a firm in the course of its business receives money or property from a third party, and the`
  line `money or property is misapplied by any of the partners while it is in the custody of the firm,`
  line
  line `the firm is liable to make good the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34654)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Holding out.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34654&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any one who by words spoken or written or by conduct represents himself, or`
  line `knowingly permits himself to be represented, to be a partner in a firm, is liable as a partner in that firm to`
  line `any one who has on the faith of any such representation given credit to the firm, whether the person`
  line `representing himself or represented to be a partner does or does not know that the representation has`
  line `reached the person so giving credit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where after a partner's death the business is continued in the old firm name, the continued use of`
  line `that name or of the deceased partner's name as a part thereof shall not itself make his legal representative`
  line `or his estate liable for any act of the firm done after his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34655)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Rights of transferee of a partner ’s interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34655&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A transfer by a partner of his interest in the`
  line `firm, either absolute or by mortgage, or by the creation by him of a charge on such interest, does not`
  line `entitle the transferee, during the continuance of the firm, to interfere in the conduct of the business, or to`
  line `require accounts, or to inspect the books of the firm, but entitles the transferee only to receive the share of`
  line `profits of the transferring partner, and the transferee shall accept the account of profits agreed to by the`
  line partners.
  line
  line `(2) If the firm is dissolved or if the transferring partner ceases to be a partner, the transferee is entitled`
  line `as against the remaining partners to receive the share of the assets of the firm to which the transferring`
  line `partner is entitled, and, for the purpose of ascertaining that share, to an account as from the date of the`
  line dissolution.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (34656)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Minors admitted to the benefits of partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34656&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who is a minor according to the`
  line `law to which he is subject may not be a partner in a firm, but, with the consent of all the partners for the`
  line `time being, he may be admitted to the benefits of partnership.`
  line
  line `(2) Such minor has a right to such share of the property and of the profits of the firm as may be`
  line `agreed upon, and he may have access to and inspect and copy any of the accounts of the firm.`
  line
  line `(3) Such minor's share is liable for the acts of the firm, but the minor is not personally liable for any`
  line `such act.`
  line
  line `(4) Such minor may not sue the partners for an account or payment of his share of the property or`
  line `profits of the firm, save when severing his connection with the firm, and in such case the amount of his`
  line `share shall be determined by a valuation made as far as possible in accordance with the rules contained in`
  line `section 48:`
  line
  line `Provided that all the partners acting together or any partner entitled to dissolve the firm upon notice to`
  line `other partners may elect in such suit to dissolve the firm, and thereupon the Court shall proceed with the`
  line `suit as one for dissolution and for settling accounts between the partners, and the amount of the share of`
  line `the minor shall be determined along with the shares of the partners.`
  line
  line `(5) At any time within six months of his attaining majority, or of his obtaining knowledge that he had`
  line `been admitted to the benefits of partnership, whichever date is later, such person may give public notice`
  line `that he has elected to become or that he has elected not to become a partner in the firm, and such notice`
  line `shall determine his position as regards the firm:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if he fails to give such notice, he shall become a partner in the firm on the expiry of the`
  line `said six months.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any person has been admitted as a minor to the benefits of partnership in a firm, the burden`
  line `of proving the fact that such person had no knowledge of such admission until a particular date after the`
  line `expiry of six months of his attaining majority shall lie on the persons asserting that fact.`
  line
  line `(7) Where such person becomes a partner,--`
  line
  line `(a) his rights and liabilities as a minor continue up to the date on which he becomes a partner, but`
  line `he also becomes personally liable to third parties for all acts of the firm done since he was admitted to`
  line `the benefits of partnership, and`
  line
  line `(b) his share in the property and profits of the firm shall be the share to which he was entitled as a`
  line minor.
  line
  line `(8) Where such person elects not to become a partner,--`
  line
  line `(a) his rights and liabilities shall continue to be those of a minor under this section up to the date`
  line `on which he gives public notice,`
  line
  line `(b) his share shall not be liable for any acts of the firm done after the date of the notice,`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) he shall be entitled to sue the partners for his share of the property and profits in accordance`
  line `with sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in sub-sections (7) and (8) shall affect the provisions of section 28.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (34657)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Introduction of a partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34657&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to contract between the partners and to the provisions of`
  line `section 30, no person shall be introduced as a partner into a firm without the consent of all the existing`
  line partners.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 30, a person who is introduced as a partner into a firm does`
  line `not thereby become liable for any act of the firm done before he became a partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (34658)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Retirement of a partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34658&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A partner may retire--`
  line
  line `(a) with the consent of all the other partners,`
  line
  line `(b) in accordance with an express agreement by the partners, or`
  line
  line `(c) where the partnership is at will, by giving notice in writing to all the other partners of his`
  line `intention to retire.`
  line
  line `(2) A retiring partner may be discharged from any liability to any third party for acts of the firm done`
  line `before his retirement by an agreement made by him with such third party and the partners of the`
  line `reconstituted firm, and such agreement may be implied by a course of dealing between such third party`
  line `and the reconstituted firm after he had knowledge of the retirement.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the retirement of a partner from a firm, he and the partners continue to`
  line `be liable as partners to third parties for any act done by any of them which would have been an`
  line `act of the firm if done before the retirement, until public notice is given of the retirement:`
  line
  line `Provided that a retired partner is not liable to any third party who deals with the firm without knowing`
  line `that he was a partner.`
  line
  line `(4) Notices under sub-section (3) may be given by the retired partner or by any partner of the`
  line `reconstituted firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (34659)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Expulsion of a partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34659&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A partner may not be expelled from a firm by any majority of the`
  line `partners, save in the exercise in good faith of powers conferred by contract between the partners.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 32 shall apply to an expelled partner as`
  line `if he were a retired partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (34660)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Insolvency of a partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34660&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a partner in a firm is adjudicated an insolvent he ceases`
  line `to be a partner on the date on which the order of adjudication is made, whether or not the firm is`
  line `thereby dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) Where under a contract between the partners the firm is not dissolved by the adjudication of a`
  line `partner as an insolvent, the estate of a partner so adjudicated is not liable for any act of the firm and the`
  line `firm is not liable for any act of the insolvent, done after the date on which the order of adjudication is`
  line made.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (34661)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Liability of estate of deceased partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34661&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Where under a contract between the partners the firm`
  line `is not dissolved by the death of a partner, the estate of a deceased partner is not liable for any act of the`
  line `firm done after his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (34662)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Rights of outgoing partner to carry on competing business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34662&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) An outgoing partner may carry on a business competing with that of the firm and he may`
  line `advertise such business, but, subject to contract to the contrary, he may not--`
  line
  line `(a) use the firm name,`
  line
  line `(b) represent himself as carrying on the business of the firm, or`
  line
  line `(c) solicit the custom of persons who were dealing with the firm before he ceased to be a partner.`
  line
  line `(2) A partner may make an agreement with his partners that on ceasing to be a partner he will not`
  line `carry on any business similar to that of the firm within a specified period or within specified local limits;`
  line `and, notwithstanding anything contained in section 27 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), such`
  line `agreement shall be valid if the restrictions imposed are reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (34663)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Right of outgoing partner in certain cases to share subsequent profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34663&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Where any member`
  line `of a firm has died or otherwise ceased to be a partner, and the surviving or continuing partners carry on`
  line `the business of the firm with the property of the firm without any final settlement of accounts as between`
  line `them and the outgoing partner or his estate, then, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, the outgoing`
  line `partner or his estate is entitled at the option of himself or his representatives to such share of the profits`
  line `made since he ceased to be a partner as may be attributable to the use of his share of the property of the`
  line `firm or to interest at the rate of six per cent. per annum on the amount of his share in the property of the`
  line `firm:`
  line
  line `Provided that where by contract between the partners an option is given to surviving or continuing`
  line `partners to purchase the interest of a deceased or outgoing partner, and that option is duly exercised, the`
  line `estate of the deceased partner, or the outgoing partner or his estate, as the case may be, is not entitled to`
  line `any further or other share of profits; but if any partner assuming to act in exercise of the option does not`
  line `in all material respects comply with the terms thereof, he is liable to account under the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (34664)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Revocation of continuing guarantee by change in firm.`
  content `A continuing guarantee given to a firm, or to a third party in respect of the transactions of a firm, is, in the absence of agreement to the contrary, revoked as to future transactions from the date of any change in the constitution of the firm.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34664&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (34665)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Dissolution of a firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34665&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The dissolution of partnership between all the partners of a firm is called`
  line `the dissolution of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (34666)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Dissolution by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34666&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `A firm may be dissolved with the consent of all the partners or in`
  line `accordance with a contract between the partners.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (34667)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Compulsory dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34667&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `A firm is dissolved--`
  line
  line `(a) by the adjudication of all the partners or of all the partners but one as insolvent, or`
  line
  line `(b) by the happening of any event which makes it unlawful for the business of the firm to be`
  line `carried on or for the partners to carry it on in partnership :`
  line
  line `Provided that, where more than one separate adventure or undertaking is carried on by the firm, the`
  line `illegality of one or more shall not of itself cause the dissolution of the firm in respect of its lawful`
  line `adventures and undertakings.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (34668)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Dissolution on the happening of certain contingencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34668&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the`
  line `partners a firm is dissolved--`
  line
  line `(a) if constituted for a fixed term, by the expiry of that term;`
  line
  line `(b) if constituted to carry out one or more adventures or undertakings, by the completion thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) by the death of a partner; and`
  line
  line `(d) by the adjudication of a partner as an insolvent.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (34669)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Dissolution by notice of partnership at will.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34669&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the partnership is at will, the firm may`
  line `be dissolved by any partner giving notice in writing to all the other partners of his intention to dissolve the`
  line firm.
  line
  line `(2) The firm is dissolved as from the date mentioned in the notice as the date of dissolution or, if no`
  line `date is so mentioned, as from the date of the communication of the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (34670)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Dissolution by the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34670&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `At the suit of a partner, the Court may dissolve a firm on any of the`
  line `following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that a partner has become of unsound mind, in which case the suit may be brought as well by`
  line `the next friend of the partner who has become of unsound mind as by any other partner;`
  line
  line `(b) that a partner, other than the partner suing, has become in any way permanently incapable of`
  line `performing his duties as partner;`
  line
  line `(c) that a partner, other than the partner suing, is guilty of conduct which is likely to affect`
  line `prejudicially the carrying on of the business, regard being had to the nature of the business;`
  line
  line `(d) that a partner, other than the partner suing, wilfully or persistently commits breach of`
  line `agreements relating to the management of the affairs of the firm or the conduct of its business, or`
  line `otherwise so conducts himself in matters relating to the business that it is not reasonably practicable`
  line `for the other partners to carry on the business in partnership with hint;`
  line
  line `(e) that a partner, other than the partner suing, has in any way transferred the whole of his interest`
  line `in the firm to a third party, or has allowed his share to be charged under the provisions of rule 49 of`
  line `Order XXI of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or has allowed it to`
  line `be sold in the recovery of arrears of land-revenue or of any dues recoverable as arrears of landrevenue due by the partner;`
  line
  line `(f) that the business of the firm cannot be carried on save at a loss; or`
  line
  line `(g) on any ground which renders it just and equitable that the firm should be dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (34671)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Liability for acts of partners done after dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34671&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding the dissolution of a`
  line `firm, the partners continue to be liable as such to third parties for any act done by any of them which`
  line `would have been an act of the firm if done before the dissolution, until public notice is given of the`
  line `dissolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that the estate of a partner who dies, or who is adjudicated an insolvent, or of a partner who,`
  line `not having been known to the person dealing with the firm to be a partner, retires from the firm, is not`
  line `liable under this section for acts done after the date on which he ceases to be a partner.`
  line
  line `(2) Notices under sub-section (1) may be given by any partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (34672)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Right of partners to have business wound up after dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34672&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `On the dissolution of a`
  line `firm every partner or his representative is entitled, as against all the other partners or their`
  line `representatives, to have the property of the firm applied in payment of the debts and liabilities of the firm, and to have the surplus distributed among the partners or their representatives according to their`
  line rights.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (34673)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Continuing authority of partners for purposes of winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34673&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `After the dissolution of a firm`
  line `the authority of each partner to bind the firm, and the other mutual rights and obligations of the partners,`
  line `continue notwithstanding the dissolution, so far as may be necessary to wind up the affairs of the firm and`
  line `to complete transactions begun but unfinished at the time of the dissolution, but not otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the firm is in no case bound by the acts of a partner who has been adjudicated insolvent;`
  line `but this proviso does not affect the liability of any person who has after the adjudication represented`
  line `himself or knowingly permitted himself to be represented as a partner of the insolvent.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (34674)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Mode of settlement of accounts between partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34674&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `In settling the accounts of a firm after`
  line `dissolution, the following rules shall, subject to agreement by the partners, be observed: --`
  line
  line `(a) Losses, including deficiencies of capital, shall be paid first out of profits, next out of capital,`
  line `and, lastly, if necessary, by the partners individually in the proportions in which they were entitled to`
  line `share profits.`
  line
  line `(b) The assets of the firm, including any sums contributed by the partners to make up deficiencies`
  line `of capital, shall be applied in the following manner and order:--`
  line
  line `(i) in paying the debts of the firm to third parties;`
  line
  line `(ii) in paying to each partner rateably what is due to him from the firm for advances as`
  line `distinguished from capital;`
  line
  line `(iii) in paying to each partner rateably what is due to him on account of capital; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the residue, if any, shall be divided among the partners in the proportions in which they`
  line `were entitled to share profits.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (34675)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Payment of firm debts and of separate debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34675&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where there are joint debts due from the firm,`
  line `and also separate debts due from any partner, the property of the firm shall be applied in the first instance`
  line `in payment of the debts of the firm, and, if there is any surplus, then the share of each partner shall be`
  line `applied in payment of his separate debts or paid to him. The separate property of any partner shall be`
  line `applied first, in the payment of his separate debts, and the surplus (if any) in the payment of the debts of`
  line `the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (34676)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Personal profits earned after dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34676&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Subject to contract between the partners, the`
  line `provisions of clause (a) of section 16 shall apply to transactions by any surviving partner or by the`
  line `representatives of a deceased partner, undertaken after the firm is dissolved on account of the death of a`
  line `partner and before its affairs have been completely wound up:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any partner or his representative has bought the goodwill of the firm, nothing in`
  line `this section shall affect his right to use the firm name.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (34677)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Return of premium on premature dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34677&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Where a partner has paid a premium on`
  line `entering into partnership for a fixed term, and the firm is dissolved before the expiration of that term`
  line `otherwise than by the death of a partner, he shall be entitled to repayment of the premium or of such part`
  line `thereof as may be reasonable, regard being had to the terms upon which he became a partner and to the`
  line `length of time during which he was a partner, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the dissolution is mainly due to his own misconduct, or`
  line
  line `(b) the dissolution is in pursuance of an agreement containing no provision for the return of the`
  line `premium or any part of it.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (34678)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Rights where partnership contract is rescinded for fraud or misrepresentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34678&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `contract creating partnership is rescinded on the ground of the fraud or misrepresentation of any of the parties thereto, the party entitled to rescind is, without prejudice to any other right, entitled--`
  line
  line `(a) to a lien on, or a right of retention of, the surplus or the assets of the firm remaining after the`
  line `debts of the firm have been paid, for any sum paid by him for the purchase of a share in the firm and`
  line `for any capital contributed by him;`
  line
  line `(b) to rank as a creditor of the firm in respect of any payment made by him towards the debts of`
  line `the firm; and`
  line
  line `(c) to be indemnified by the partner or partners guilty of the fraud or misrepresentation against all`
  line `the debts of the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (34679)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Right to restrain from use of firm name or firm property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34679&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `After a firm is dissolved, every`
  line `partner or his representative may, in the absence of a contract between the partners to the contrary,`
  line `restrain any other partner or his representative from carrying on a similar business in the firm name or`
  line `from using any of the property of the firm for his own benefit, until the affairs of the firm have been`
  line `completely wound up:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any partner or his representative has bought the goodwill of the firm, nothing in`
  line `this section shall affect his right to use the firm name.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (34680)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Agreements in restraint of trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34680&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Partners may, upon or in anticipation of the dissolution of`
  line `the firm, make an agreement that some or all of them will not carry on a business similar to that of the`
  line `firm within a specified period or within specified local limits; and notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 27 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), such agreement shall be valid if the restrictions`
  line `imposed are reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (34681)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Sale of goodwill after dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34681&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) In settling the accounts of a firm after dissolution, the goodwill shall, subject to`
  line `contract between the partners, be included in the assets, and it may be sold either separately or along with`
  line `other property of the firm.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the goodwill of a firm is sold after dissolution, a partner may carry on a business`
  line `competing with that of the buyer and he may advertise such business, but, subject to agreement between`
  line `him and the buyer, he may not--`
  line
  line `(a) use the firm name,`
  line
  line `(c) represent himself as carrying on the business of the firm, or`
  line
  line `(c) solicit the custom of persons who were dealing with the firm before its dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) Any partner may, upon the sale of the goodwill of a firm, make an agreement with the buyer that`
  line `such partner will not carry on any business similar to that of the firm within a specified period or within`
  line `specified local limits, and, notwithstanding anything contained in section 27 of the Indian Contract Act,`
  line `1872 (9 of 1872), such agreement shall be valid if the restrictions imposed are reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (34682)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to exempt from application of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34682&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government of any State]`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to`
  line `^2[that State] or to any part thereof specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G. G. in C.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "any province".`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (34683)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Appointment of Registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34683&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint Registrars of Firms for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, and may define the areas within which they shall exercise their powers and perform`
  line `their duties.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Registrar shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (34684)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34684&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registration of a firm may be effected at any time by`
  line `sending by post or delivering to the Registrar of the area in which any place of business of the firm is`
  line `situated or proposed to be situated, a statement in the prescribed form and accompanied by the prescribed`
  line `fee, stating--`
  line
  line `(a) the firm name,`
  line
  line `(b) the place or principal place of business of the firm,`
  line
  line `(c) the names of any other places where the firm carries on business,`
  line
  line `(d) the date when each partner joined the firm,`
  line
  line `(e) the names in full and permanent addresses of the partners, and`
  line
  line `(f) the duration of the firm.`
  line
  line `The statement shall be signed by all the partners, or by their agents specially authorised in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Each person signing the statement shall also verify it in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A firm name shall not contain any of the following words, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Crown", "Emperor", "Empress", "Empire", "Imperial", "King", "Queen", "Royal", or words`
  line `expressing or implying the sanction, approval or patronage of ^1*** Government ^2***,except ^3[when`
  line `the State Government] signifies ^4[its] consent to the use of such words as part of the firm name by`
  line `order in writing ^5***`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Goa, Daman and Diu.--`
  line
  line `The Government of Goa is hereby pleased to levy a non-refundable processing fee of Rs.`
  line `1,000/- (Rupees one thousand only) for processing the documents for registration of Partnership`
  line `Firm under the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (Central Act 9 of 1932).`
  line
  line `This Order shall come into force with effect from the 1st day of April, 2017.`
  line
  line `(Published in the Official Gazette Series I No. 52 (Extraordinary-2) dated 31-3-2017) (w.e.f. 8-5-2017-`
  line `LD(Estt.) (C)/407 dated 31-3-2017)`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 58.--In the Indian Partnership Act, 1932, (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `Principal Act) section 58 shall be substituted as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `58. Application for registration.--(1) The registration of a firm may be effected at any time by`
  line `uploading on the website following statement in the prescribed online form and accompanied with`
  line `prescribed fees to the Registrar of the area in which any place of business of the firm is situated or`
  line `proposed to be situated, stating.--`
  line
  line `(a) the firm name,`
  line
  line `(b) the place or principal place of business of the firm,`
  line
  line `(c) the names of any other places where the firm carries on business,`
  line
  line `(d) the date when each partner joined the firm,`
  line
  line `(e) the names in full and permanent addresses of the partners, and`
  line
  line `(f) the duration of the film.`
  line
  line `The statement shall be digitally signed by all the partners or by their agents specially authorized`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The applicant, signing the statement shall also upload to the website, verifying the statement`
  line `recorded in the online format mentioned in sub-section (1), verifying it in the affidavit certified by the`
  line `Notary on the non-judicial stamp paper of Rs. 10/.`
  line
  line `(3) The desired enclosed shall also be uploaded on website, by the applicant.`
  line
  line `(4) A firm name shall not contain the word Union, State, Land Mortgage, Land development,`
  line `Cooperative, Gandhi, Reserve Bank or any of the words expressing or implying the sanction, approval or`
  line `patronage of Government, except when the State Government signifies its consent to the use of such`
  line `words as part of the firm name by order in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) The prescribed fee of registration shall be submitted online after the online approval given by the`
  line Registrar.
  line
  line `(6) After submitting the prescribed registration fee the digitally signed registration certificate may be`
  line `downloaded from the website by the applicant.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 5 of 2019, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the Crown or the Central Government or any Provincial" omitted by the A. O. 1950. The words "the Central`
  line `Government or any Provincial Government or the Crown Representative" were subs. by the A. O. 1937 for "the G. of I. or a L.`
  line `G."`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the Crown Representative" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "when the G.G. in C.".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. ibid. for "his"`
  line
  line `5. The words "under the hand of one of the Secretaries to the G. of I." omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (34685)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34685&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where the Registrar is satisfied that the provisions of section 58 have been duly`
  line `complied with, he shall record an entry of the statement in a register called the Register of Firms, and`
  line `shall file the statement.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 59A.--In section 59A of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (Central Act IX of`
  line `1932), in sub-section (1), for the words "by reason of the reorganization of States, the words, figures and`
  line `brackets "by reason of the addition of the Bellary District to the State of Mysore under the Andhra State`
  line `Act, 1953 (Central Act XXX of 1953), or of the reorganization of States under the States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956 (Central Act 37 of 1956)" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 19 of 1961, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 59A--1 of IX of 1932.-In section 59A-1 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932`
  line `(IX of 1932), in its application to the State of Maharashtra (hereinafter referred to as "the principal Act"),`
  line `for the words "one hundred rupees" the words "one thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 16 of 2018, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (34686)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Recording of alterations in firm name and principal place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34686&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an`
  line `alteration is made in the firm name or in the location of the principal place of business of a registered`
  line `firm, a statement may be sent to the Registrar accompanied by the prescribed fee, specifying the`
  line `alteration, and signed and verified in the manner required under section 58.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Registrar is satisfied that the provisions of sub-section (1) have been duly complied`
  line `with, he shall amend the entry relating to the firm in the Register of Firms in accordance with the`
  line `statement, and shall file it along with the statement relating to the firm filed under section 59.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (34687)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Noting of closing and opening of branches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34687&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `When a registered firm discontinues business at`
  line `any place or begins to carry or business at any place, such place not being its principal place of business,`
  line `any partner or agent of the firm may send intimation thereof to the Registrar, who shall make a note of`
  line `such intimation in the entry relating to the firm in the Register of Firms, and shall file the intimation along`
  line `with the statement relating to the firm filed under section 59.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (34688)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Noting of changes in names and addresses of partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34688&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `When any partner in a registered firm`
  line `alters his name or permanent address, an intimation of the alteration may be sent by any partner or agent`
  line `of the firm to the Registrar, who shall deal with it in the manner provided in section 61.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (34689)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Recording of changes in and dissolution of a firm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34689&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `When a change occurs in the constitution of a registered firm any incoming, continuing or outgoing`
  line `partner, and when a registered firm is dissolved any person who was a partner immediately before the dissolution, or the agent of any such partner or person specially authorised in this behalf, may give notice`
  line `to the Registrar of such change or dissolution, specifying the date thereof; and the Registrar shall make a`
  line `record of the notice in the entry relating to the firm in the Register of Firms, and shall file the notice along`
  line `with the statement relating to the firm filed under section 59.`
  line
  line `(2) When a minor who has been admitted to the benefits of partnership in a firm attains majority and`
  line `elects to become or not to become a partner, and the firm is then a registered firm, he, or his agent`
  line `specially authorised in this behalf, may give notice to the Registrar that he has or has not become a`
  line `partner, and the Registrar shall deal with the notice in the manner provided in sub-section (1)`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (34690)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34690&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shill have power at all times to rectify any mistake`
  line `in order to bring the entry in the Register of Firms relating to any firm into conformity with the`
  line `documents relating to that firm filed under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) On application made by all the parties who have signed any document relating to a firm filed`
  line `under this Chapter, the Registrar may rectify any mistake in such document or in the record or note`
  line `thereof made in the Register of Firms.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (34691)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Amendment of Register by order of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34691&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `A Court deciding any matter relating to a`
  line `registered firm may direct that the Registrar shall make any amendment in the entry in the Register of`
  line `Firms relating to such firm which is consequential upon its decision; and the Registrar shall amend the`
  line `entry accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (34692)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Inspection of Register and filed documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34692&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Register of Firms shall be open to`
  line `inspection by any person on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) All statements, notices and intimations filed under this Chapter shall be open to inspection,`
  line `subject to such conditions and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (34693)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Grant of copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34693&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar shall on application furnish to any person, on payment of such`
  line `fee as may be prescribed, a copy, certified under his hand, of any entry or portion thereof in the Register`
  line `of Firms.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Substituted of section 67.--In Principal Act, section 67 shall be substituted as follow, namely:--`
  line
  line `67. Grant of copies.--The Registrar shall on online application furnish to any person, on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be prescribed , a copy digitally certified under his hand of any entry or`
  line `portion thereof in the register of firms.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 5 of 2019, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (34694)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Rules of evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34694&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any statement, intimation or notice recorded or noted in the Register of`
  line `Firms shall, as against any person by whom or on whose behalf such statement, intimation or notice was`
  line `signed, be conclusive proof of any fact therein stated.`
  line
  line `(2) A certified copy of an entry relating to a firm in the Register of Firms may be produced in proof`
  line `of the fact of the registration of such firm, and of the contents of any statement, intimation or notice`
  line `recorded or noted therein.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 68.--In Principal Act, sub-section (1) of section 68 shall be substituted as`
  line `follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `68. Rules of Evidence:--(1) Any statement, intimation or notice recorded or noted in the register`
  line `of Firms shall, as against any person by whom or on whose behalf such statement, intimation or`
  line `notice was digitally signed, be conclusive proof of any fact therein stated.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 5 of 2019, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (34695)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Effect of non-registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34695&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit to enforce a right arising from a contract or conferred by`
  line `this Act shall be institutes in any Court by or on behalf of any person suing as a partner in a firm against`
  line `the firm or any person alleged to be or to have been a partner in the firm unless the firm is registered and`
  line `the person suing is or has been shown in the Register of Firms as a partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit to enforce a tight arising from a contract shall be instituted in any Court by or on behalf of`
  line `a firm against any third party unless the firm is registered and the persons suing are or have been shown`
  line `in the Register of Firms as partners in the firm.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply also to a claim of set-off or other proceeding`
  line `to enforce a right arising from a contract, but shall not affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the enforcement of any right to sue for the dissolution of a firm or for accounts of a dissolved`
  line `firm, or a ay right or power to realise the property of a dissolved firm, or`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of an official assignee, receiver or Court under the Presidency-towns Insolvency`
  line `Act, 1909 (2 of 1909), or the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), to realise the property of`
  line `an insolvent partner.`
  line
  line `(4) This section shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to firms or to partners in firms which have no place of business in ^1[the territories to which`
  line `this Act extends], or whose places of business in ^2[the said territories] are situated in areas to which,`
  line `by notification under ^3[section 56], this Chapter does not apply, or`
  line
  line `(b) to any suit or claim of set-off not exceeding one hundred rupees in value which, in the`
  line `Presidency-towns, is not of a kind specified in section 19 of the Presidency Small Cause Courts Act,`
  line `1882 (15 of 1882), or, outside the Presidency-towns, is not of a kind specified in the Second Schedule`
  line `to the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887 (9 of 1887), or to any proceeding in execution or`
  line `other proceeding incidental to or arising from any such suit or claim.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Substitution of section 69A of IX of 1932.--For section 69A of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"69A. Charges for delay in compliance of section 60, 61, 62 or 63.--If any statement, intimation or`
  line `notice under section 60, 61, 62 or as the case may be, 63, in respect of any registered firm is not sent or`
  line `given to the Registrar, within the period specified in that section, the Registrar may, make suitable`
  line `amendments in the records relating to the firm, upon payment of charges for delay in sending or giving`
  line `the same, at the rate of rupees two thousand per year or part thereof in respect of the period between the`
  line `date of expiry of the period specified in that section and the date of making the payment.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 16 of 2018, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "Part A States and Part C States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3 and the Schedule, ibid., for "such States".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1934, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "section 55".`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (34696)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Penalty for furnishing false particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34696&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Any person who signs any statement, amending`
  line `statement, notice or intimation under this Chapter containing any particular which he knows to be false or`
  line `does not believe to be true, or containing particulars which he knows to be incomplete or does not believe`
  line `to be complete, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (34697)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34697&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] ^2[may by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette make rules] prescribing the fees which shall accompany documents sent to the Registrar of Firms,`
  line `or which shall be payable for the inspection of documents in the custody of the Registrar of Firms, or for`
  line `copies from the Register of Firms:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fees shall not exceed the maximum fees specified in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may ^3[also] make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the form of statement submitted under section 58, and of the verification thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring statements, intimations and notices under sections 60, 61, 62 and 63 to be in`
  line `prescribed form, and prescribing the form thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the form of the Register of Firms, and the mode in which entries relating to firms`
  line `are to be made therein, and the mode in which such entries are to be amended or notes made therein;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the procedure of the Registrar when disputes arise;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the filing of documents received by the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribing conditions for the inspection of original documents;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the grant of copies;`
  line
  line `(h) regulating the elimination of registers and documents;`
  line
  line `(i) providing for the maintenance and form of an index to the Register of Firms; and`
  line
  line `(j) generally, to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be subject to the condition of previous publication.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as it is made,`
  line `before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G.G. in C.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "may make rules" (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (34698)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Mode of giving public notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34698&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `A public notice under this Act is given--`
  line
  line `(a) where it relates to the retirement or expulsion of a partner from a registered firm, or to the`
  line `dissolution of a registered firm, or to the election to become or not to become a partner in a registered`
  line `firm by a person attaining majority who was admitted as a minor to the benefits of partnership, by`
  line `notice to the Registrar of Firms under section 63, and by publication in the Official Gazette and in at`
  line `least one vernacular newspaper circulating in the district where the firm to which it relates has its`
  line `place or principal place of business, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, by publication in the Official Gazette and in at least one vernacular`
  line `newspaper circulating in the district where the firm to which it relates has its place or principal place`
  line `of business.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (34699)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeals.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34699&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (34700)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460&sectionId=34700&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00012_193209_1523350631460
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act or any repeal effected thereby shall affect or be deemed to affect--`
  line
  line `(a) any right, title, interest, obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) any legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, title, interest, obligation or`
  line `liability, or anything done or suffered before the commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(c) anything done or suffered before the commencement of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(d) any enactment relating to partnership not expressly repealed by this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) any rule of insolvency relating to partnership, or`
  line
  line `(f) any rule of law not inconsistent with this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
